## Core API Reference

Run the local FastAPI app:

```bash
pip install "cortex-persist[api]"
uvicorn cortex.api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8484
```

Useful local links:

- [Local API health](http://localhost:8484/health)
- [Local API status](http://localhost:8484/v1/status)
- [Local interactive API docs](http://localhost:8484/docs)

Export the OpenAPI document:

```bash
python -c "from cortex.api.openapi import export_openapi_spec; print(export_openapi_spec())"
```

Default core endpoints:

| Area | Endpoints |
| --- | --- |
| Health | `GET /health`, `GET /v1/status` |
| Facts | `POST /v1/facts`, `POST /v1/facts/batch`, `GET /v1/facts`, `GET /v1/facts/{fact_id}` |
| Project recall | `GET /v1/projects/{project}/facts` |
| Search | `POST /v1/facts/search` |
| History and lineage | `GET /v1/facts/{fact_id}/history`, `GET /v1/facts/{fact_id}/chain` |
| Ledger | `GET /v1/ledger/status`, `GET /v1/ledger/verify`, `POST /v1/ledger/checkpoint` |
| Admin keys | `POST /v1/admin/keys`, `GET /v1/admin/keys` |
| Trust | `POST /v1/trust/guard`, `GET /v1/trust/profiles/{agent_id}`, `GET /v1/trust/compliance` |
| Export | `GET /v1/projects/{project}/export` |

Authentication uses Bearer tokens created through the admin key surface:

```bash
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8484/v1/admin/keys?name=dev-client&tenant_id=default"

curl -H "Authorization: Bearer ctx_your_key" \
  http://localhost:8484/v1/status
```

Experimental API routes are opt-in and must be documented as such:

```bash
CORTEX_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_API=1 uvicorn cortex.api:app --port 8484
```

## SDK Examples

### Python In-Process Engine

Use this first when the caller runs in the same Python process as CORTEX.

```python
import asyncio
from cortex import CortexEngine


async def main() -> None:
    engine = CortexEngine()
    try:
        fact_id = await engine.store(
            project="dev-agent",
            content="CORTEX Persist stores facts with ledger continuity.",
            fact_type="knowledge",
        )
        results = await engine.search("ledger continuity", project="dev-agent")
        ledger = await engine.verify_ledger()

        print(f"fact_id={fact_id}")
        print(f"matches={len(results)}")
        print(f"ledger_valid={ledger.get('valid')}")
    finally:
        await engine.close()


asyncio.run(main())
```

### Python HTTP Client

Use this when the REST API is running separately.

```python
from cortex.api.client import CortexClient


client = CortexClient("http://localhost:8484", api_key="ctx_your_key")
try:
    fact_id = client.store(
        project="dev-agent",
        content="CORTEX Persist can be accessed over HTTP.",
        fact_type="knowledge",
    )
    results = client.search("HTTP access", project="dev-agent")
    status = client.status()
finally:
    client.close()
```

### TypeScript SDK

The TypeScript SDK source lives in [sdks/js](sdks/js). It targets Node 18+
and uses native `fetch`.

```typescript
import { Cortex } from '@cortex-persist/sdk'

const cortex = new Cortex({
  url: 'http://localhost:8484',
  apiKey: 'ctx_your_key',
})

const factId = await cortex.store(
  'CORTEX Persist exposes a TypeScript HTTP client.',
  { project: 'dev-agent', factType: 'knowledge' },
)

const facts = await cortex.search('TypeScript HTTP client', {
  project: 'dev-agent',
  topK: 5,
})

const ledger = await cortex.verify()
console.log({ factId, matches: facts.length, ledgerValid: ledger.valid })
```

### cURL Smoke Test

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8484/v1/facts \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ctx_your_key" \
  -d '{
    "project": "dev-agent",
    "content": "Hello from cortexpersist.dev",
    "fact_type": "knowledge"
  }'

curl -X POST http://localhost:8484/v1/facts/search \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ctx_your_key" \
  -d '{"query": "cortexpersist.dev", "project": "dev-agent", "k": 5}'
```

## MCP Integration

Start the default stdio MCP server:

```bash
pip install "cortex-persist[mcp]"
python -m cortex.mcp
```

Recommended core tools:

- `cortex_store`
- `cortex_search`
- `cortex_status`
- `cortex_ledger_verify`

Extended MCP families require:

```bash
CORTEX_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_MCP=1 python -m cortex.mcp
```

## Test And Staging Environments

Use these links and commands when checking developer flows.

| Environment | Link or command | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Local API | [http://localhost:8484/docs](http://localhost:8484/docs) | Interactive API docs in non-production mode |
| Local API health | [http://localhost:8484/health](http://localhost:8484/health) | Readiness smoke test |
| Local MkDocs | `mkdocs serve -a 127.0.0.1:8001` | Documentation preview without colliding with API examples |
| Local prototype | `python -m http.server 8787 --directory docs/prototypes` then [http://localhost:8787/saas_landing.html](http://localhost:8787/saas_landing.html) | Static site preview |
| Astro dev site | `npm run dev` then [http://localhost:4321](http://localhost:4321) | Frontend preview |
| Public product | [https://cortexpersist.com](https://cortexpersist.com) | Product, pricing, and checkout surface |
| Public docs paths | [docs](https://cortexpersist.com/docs/), [API](https://cortexpersist.com/api/), [quickstart](https://cortexpersist.com/quickstart/) | Public documentation redirects from the static prototype deployment |
| Cloudflare edge proxy | [https://cortex-persist-web.pages.dev/v1/health](https://cortex-persist-web.pages.dev/v1/health) | Staging/API proxy target referenced by `docs/prototypes/vercel.json` |
| Vercel API preview | `https://<vercel-preview>/v1/health` | Serverless checkout/API preview configured through `CORTEX_API_ORIGIN` |

Do not publish secrets or bypass headers in this file. Protected Vercel previews
may require `VERCEL_AUTOMATION_BYPASS_SECRET`, but that value belongs in the
deployment environment only.

## Publication Checklist

Before treating `cortexpersist.dev` as current:

```bash
mkdocs build --strict
python -c "from cortex.api.openapi import export_openapi_spec; print(export_openapi_spec())"
npm --prefix sdks/js run build
python -m pytest tests/test_compliance_sdk.py -q
git diff --check
```

If a command cannot run in the current checkout, record the exact blocker in the
release notes instead of silently skipping it.

## Boundary Notes

- The in-process Python engine is the recommended first integration surface.
- The TypeScript SDK is an HTTP client for callers outside the Python process.
- Public docs should describe the default core API first.
- Experimental CLI, API, and MCP surfaces must remain behind their explicit
  `CORTEX_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_*` gates.
- Production deployments should not expose `/docs`; use exported OpenAPI
  artifacts for public API reference pages.
